We'd like you to meet <b>Napper</b>, our featured Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Napper has been kicking back and relaxing at his Lakeview pad, at <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=marc272727"><a href='/home/?user=marc272727'>27974-C Aldan Lake</a></a>, since November 18th, 2007. He loves being on the lake and feeling the crisp wind blowing off the water. <br><br>In a little over a year, Napper has made racking up gold trophies look easy. He's collected honors from the likes of Hop-n-Drop, Sink Three, Rope Climb, Home Run Derby, and Intergalactic Defender. <br><br>Napper describes himself as very clever, deep thinking, and a little comical. He sure does put his brain to good use&mdash;and he's even got the Sudoku trophy to prove it. <br><br>Martial arts, magic tricks, and math are just a few of Napper's interests. With hobbies like that, he could easily become the first vanishing ninja-mathematician. <br><br>When Napper's not crunching numbers or doing roundhouse kicks, he's likely to be jamming out to some of his favorite tunes. He enjoys listening to jazz, classical music, and classic rock. <br><br>If you happen to bump into Napper on the street, shake his hand and thank him for being such an outstanding Citizen of the Week!<br><br><br></div>
